Mexico Stocks: Alfa, Cemex, Empresas Ica, Walmex Shares Advance

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-08-09T20:20:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/mexico-stocks-alfa-cemex-empresas-ica-walmex-shares-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index gained 2.1 percent to 32,381.55  Mexican companies whose stocks tumbled more than 10 percent
yesterday in the global rout erased some of their losses today
as the  Federal Reserve  said it was prepared to use a range of
tools to bolster the economy.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of
aluminum engine heads, jumped 4.1 percent to 148.03 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, gained 3.9 percent to 6.46 pesos.  Controladora Comercial Mexicana SAB (COMERUBC MM), the
Mexican supermarket chain that defaulted on debt in 2008, jumped
10.7 percent to 17.86 pesos.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA* MM), the country’s biggest
construction company, advanced 7.2 percent to 17.76 pesos.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB (WALMEXV MM),  Latin America ’s
largest retailer, advanced 1 percent to 30.42 pesos. The company
said same-store sales rose 3.9 percent in July, according to
statement e-mailed yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
